===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|now|rare}} The act of [[cutting]] or [[carving]] something; a [[stroke]] or [[slice]].
# The [[groove]] or [[slit]] created by cutting or sawing something; an [[incision]].
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1999|passage=They pass through a cleft that has been made across a low range of hills, like a '''kerf''' in the top of a log, and enter into a lovely territory of subtly swelling emerald green fields strewn randomly with small white capsules that he takes to be sheep.|author=[[w:Neal Stephenson|Neal Stephenson]]|title=Cryptonomicon}}
# The distance between [[diverge|diverging]] [[saw]] [[teeth]].
#* '''1991''', [[w:Popular Mechanics|Popular Mechanics]], January issue, [http://books.google.ru/books?id=feMDAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA63&ots=5KtnX0zrbr&dq=kerf&pg=PA63#v=onepage&q=kerf&f=false page 63], "Thin-kerf blades", by Rosario Capotostro
#*: Sawing with a thin-'''kerf''' blade produces a kerf that's 1/2 to 1/3 the size of a standard blade '''kerf'''.
# The flattened, cut-off end of a [[branch]] or [[tree]]; a [[stump]] or sawn-off cross-section.
#*{{quote-book|en|1941|{{w|Vladimir Nabokov}}|The Real Life of Sebastian Knight|edition=Penguin 1971|page=115
|passage=Sebastian, still not alone, is seated on the white-and-cinder-grey trunk of a felled tree. […] A Camberwell Beauty skims past and settles on the '''kerf''', fanning its velvety wings.}}
# The portion or quantity (e.g. of [[hay]], [[turf]], [[wool]], etc.) cut off in a given stroke.

